{
  "title": "ISic003391. Opus signinum inscription of Gnaius Modius",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γναΐου Μοδίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Γναΐου\"><span data-text=\"Γναΐου\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">Γναΐου</span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Μοδίου\"><span data-text=\"Μοδίου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">Μοδίου</span></span></span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γναΐου Μοδίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Γναΐου\"><span data-text=\"Γναΐου\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ΓΝΑΙΟΥ</span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Μοδίου\"><span data-text=\"Μοδίου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ΜΟΔΙΟΥ</span></span></span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003391_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391_leftdetail_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_leftdetail_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391_leftdetail.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_leftdetail-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391_rightdetail_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_rightdetail_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391_rightdetail.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_rightdetail-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391_context_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_context_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003391_context.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_context-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>(House of) Gnaius Modius</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Archaeologically, the 'baths of Cnaius Modius' (so called because of this inscription at the entrance) should be dated to the first century BC (so Tréziny 2018: 274), not the third-century BC as discussed in Torelli 2007</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 2007.0671 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283</a>  </li><li> 59.1107 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> 26.1102 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> Manni Piraino 1975 152 no.18 tav.34.3 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001772\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001772</a>  </li><li> Torelli 2007 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001558\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001558</a>  </li><li> Tréziny 2018 273-274 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002599\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002599</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Letters neatly formed of small black basalt stone chips. Nu has a shorter right hand vertical; omicron is equal size to the other letters; alpha off vertical, cross-bar formed by single piece; mu formed by four equal off-vertical strokes, mid-point descending fully to the base-line.</p> Line 1 <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Δ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Δ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> </p>    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence </div>",
